723752f-a.text:
117 and 125-135 Varick Street (The American News Building), west side, at Dominick Street. Nos. 123 and 119-121, at and adjoining the S.W. corner, have been demolished. The American News Building. on the west side from Dominick to Spring Streets, was built about 1923.
February 12, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

719328f-a.text:
Dominick Street, south side, from Varick Street to Sixth Avenue, showing the old frame house No. 14 and the Dominick Street side of Public School No. 38, at and adjoining what is now the west side of Sixth Avenue but used to be Clark Street. There used to be three more old houses in the block,Nos. 16-20 Dominick Street, adjoining the corner of Varick Street; they were taken down not
long after 1922.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 581.

Varick Street, south from Dominick Street. In the background, on the east side of the street, may be seen the spire of St. John's Chapel. This picture was taken before the widening of Varick Street
(at the expense of the east side) in 1914-15.
About 1912.

127-29 Varick Street, adjoining and north of the N. W. corner of Dominick Street, showing two frame 2 1-2 story residences. The buildings at the left and right margins are also of frame construction; that at the left (corner structure) having a brick shell. Note the alley that
separates No's. 129 and 131.
About 1900
J. J. Corell, photo
